"Hi Everyone,

title: For Sale:  CZ Custom CZ "Compact L" 9mm Custom gun, Xtra Cust work Night Sights VZ Grips & Xtra Shadow Mag $1K
postcontent:
Im selling my 200 round used, but in absolutely brand new shape, two month old CZ Custom in Mesa, Arizona "CZ Custom Compact L" 9mm. What in the heck is a compact L you ask? Looks like a P-01 doesnt it. Not at all. They do start with the compact frame like a cz p-01. But thats where that ends. Think of it as a baby shadow 9. They start with all new frames and slides in the black and custom fit like a perfect match gun. It's very, very tight. Unlike the P-01 it's got a manual safety instead of a decocker also like a shadow. Next they smooth the trigger cam, sear area, the frame, the rail surfaces, the ramp and bullet throat. The Barrel overall interior and exterior & chamber are all polished as well. Then they respring the entire gun, resight it and install the combat CZ custom hammer. CZ night sights are included. Also I had them smooth the inside of the rails as well and swap the firing pin for titanium. It's by far the smoothest double action gun ive ever fired including many smooth old smith revolvers. Breaks like glass. And obviously the single action trigger is also nice. Not dangerously light. Says 3.5 lbs on the factory sheets. The CZ custom's test target compared to the CZ factory Czech target speaks for itself. This gun is VERY, very accurate. I also included VZ Frag Dirty Olive grips and original rubber CZ factory grips which are also super grippy. The VZs were $80. It originally came with two 14 round CZ (MecGar) factory mags. It come with that PLUS an EXTRA CZ factory Shadow SP-01 19 round mag with extended baseplate. This is a $50 mag by itself that im throwing in for nothing smile
$1k Firm for everything or $970 without the 19 round Shadow Mag.
